org.dellroad.muxable

Interface NestedChannelRequest


  • public interface NestedChannelRequest
    Represents nested channel(s) newly created by the remote side.

    The input and output channels operate independently: for example, closing one does not affect the other.

      • getInput

        ReadableByteChannel getInput()
        Get the input channel, if any. This corresponds to the output channel on the remote side.

        The returned channel will typically also implement InterruptibleChannel, but that is implementation-dependent.

        In some implementations, getInput() and getOutput() may return the same channel; this is explicitly permitted.

        Returns:
        the input channel associated with this instance, or null if this instance was created with only an output channel

      • getOutput

        WritableByteChannel getOutput()
        Get the output channel, if any. This corresponds to the input channel on the remote side.

        The returned channel will typically also implement InterruptibleChannel, but that is implementation-dependent.

        In some implementations, getInput() and getOutput() may return the same channel; this is explicitly permitted.

        Returns:
        the output channel associated with this instance, or null if this instance was created with only an input channel
